.TH "copy_from_user_nofault" 9 "copy_from_user_nofault" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
copy_from_user_nofault \- safely attempt to read from a user-space location
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" copy_from_user_nofault
.BI "(void *dst "  ","
.BI "const void __user *src "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
pointer to the buffer that shall take the data
.IP "src" 12
address to read from. This must be a user address.
.IP "size" 12
size of the data chunk
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Safely read from user address \fIsrc\fP to the buffer at \fIdst\fP. If a kernel fault
happens, handle that and return -EFAULT.
